Text.Value: Ya lookin' down on me as well? I can get up by myself.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player reaches out his hand, and the goblin should stare at it in disgust, before getting up on his own.

Text.Value: He wants mercy. I say show it to him - decisively.
Since when has yielding been an option? Gut the little rodent.
Leave him grovelling on the ground.
You strike your prey, then offer aid? I will never understand your kind.
You strike your prey, then offer aid? Deplorable.
Now. You should kiss my feet.
Nicely done. I probably couldn't have resisted kicking him in the teeth.
Laugh at his eagerness and finish him off.
I didn't realise we were here to make friends.
I hope you learned your lesson, young man!
Good. We've had enough party games now, I think.
A fine show of dominance. Almost sweeter than blood. Almost.
I think my point's been made. Come on, I'll help you up.
Ignore his pleading and prepare for the finishing blow.
Courtesy is quite wasted on this fellow, I see.
Gah. Arrogant pig.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The goblin gets up, then mumbles to himself.

Text.Value: Ha! My, this place is fun.
Mercy is not your strong suit, is it?
A fine show of force. The worms shall feast tonight.
There... there, I dun it.

EditorData.AnimationTags: Crusher on the ground wipes his mouth with back of his hand - RS
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The goblin is on the floor, speaking up at you. He's clearly disgusted, but he's doing his best to smile
EditorData.NodeContext: Doesn't want to offend you, but he's disgusted
EditorData.SFXTags: Crusher kissing foot continues, wiping mouth on the back of his hand

Text.Value: Leave him grovelling on the ground.
Good. No telling how many lives he might yet have taken. Tonight, the Coast breathes easier.
You could've at least let him grovel a little.
Well done. You humiliated a goblin. Let's go.
He surrendered - leave him be.
Take his head. He won't be putting it to good use.
Help! H - help me!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The goblin is on the floor, shouting for the surrounding goblins
EditorData.NodeContext: Panicked. You are about to kill him.

Text.Value: Ignore his spite, friend. Mercy is its own reward.
Did that make you feel strong? You're more pathetic than he is.
Wait! I - I yield! I yield!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The goblin is on the floor, speaking up at you. (Custom Scene for Goblin on the floor)
EditorData.NodeContext: Very panicked. They were in a fight he thought he'd win, but he's losing.
EditorData.SFXTags: Crusher hits the ground, armous clanks as he changes position out of shot, surrounding goblins gasp

Text.Value: Learned your lesson?
Best not leave any loose ends. This one might reward mercy with backstabbing.
All that, and you'd give him a hand? You're a fickle one, chief.
Gods. I'm not sure who to pity more for that display - you or the goblin.
Thank you. I thought you were never going to shut him up.
Leave.
Yes... yes!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The goblin scrambles to your foot.
EditorData.NodeContext: Panicked and eager to please - he's afraid you'll kill him.

Text.Value: How about you make him kiss your feet next? Pungent poetic justice.
Yes... yes! Mercy!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The goblin is on the floor, speaking up at you.
EditorData.NodeContext: Panicked and eager to please - he's afraid you'll kill him.

Synopsis: We defeated the drunk goblin in a fight he started. He yields before we can kill him. He's lying on the ground.
